    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "With this big of a number, `searchable` on the normal Menu widget would make more sense IMO. Then you can use the connector to make it into a `<select>` again quite easily.\r\n\r\nYou can try changing the `maxValuesPerFacet` ([doc](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/api-parameters/maxValuesPerFacet/?language=javascript)) option in the settings of the index, but it could also be an API limitation.\r\n\r\nI'd like to see what kind of UI you're making where it makes sense to have 10k items in a single `<select>`",
    "created_at": "2018-07-27T08:02:14Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3043#issuecomment-408343777",
